,[[,,,,[]
,6]
,"\u003cp\u003eHi, I’m Everett Bogue.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIn 2009, I quit my job and started throwing out my stuff. I’ve been living out of a backpack since. I create location independent Minimalist Businesses. I’m the author of \u003ca href\u003d\"http://www.minimalistbusiness.com/\" target\u003d\"_blank\"\u003eMinimalist Business\u003c/a\u003e. I live and work from anywhere in the world.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI’m interested in how we communicate with humans and machines on the modern web. Technology is evolving at an exponential rate –we’re evolving with it.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI’m interested in doing things that scare me. I grow and find purpose when I’m living in an uncertain world. When everyone is usually heading away from challenging things, I tend to head towards them.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI’ve authored a digital products over the last 3 years, including The Art of Being Minimalist, Minimalist Business, Augmented Humanity, Taking Your Book to the Web, Evolving Your Digital Work and a half dozen others. My current digital product is \u003ca href\u003d\"http://www.minimalistbusiness.com/\" target\u003d\"_blank\"\u003eMinimalist Business\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI’m interested in how we gather permission to contact other humans in the world. Like an Airport or a busy market in India, the Internet is a crowded place. I’d like to ask permission before I offer things to you.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eWould you be willing to \u003ca href\u003d\"http://www.evbogue.com/\" target\u003d\"_blank\"\u003ehear more from me\u003c/a\u003e?\u003cbr\u003e\u003c/p\u003e"]
,[[,,,,[]
