});</script><script>AF_initDataQueue.push({key: '4', data: [[["up","","Buzz","Everett Bogue","I was interviewed by \u003cspan class\u003d\"proflinkWrapper\"\u003e\u003cspan class\u003d\"proflinkPrefix\"\u003e+\u003c/span\u003e\u003ca href\u003d\"https://plus.google.com/108240409864554105259\" class\u003d\"proflink\" oid\u003d\"108240409864554105259\"\u003eHugo Melo\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/span\u003e about Minimalist Business marketing. \u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003eExcerpt from interview: \u0026quot;The Internet is a vast place. There’s a potential to reach anyone in the world. However, I only want to hear about a product or service if it’s going to benefit me. This is true for everyone. Packaging information is not enough, it needs to be information which benefits other people.\u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003eThe only option is to experiment with what we’re putting out into the world. If what I create today doesn’t land, I get an opportunity to try again tomorrow.\u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003eThe goal of a Minimalist Business is flexibility. It’s about keeping overhead low so the business can change with a world in flux. It’s by growing, challenging, evolving myself that I’m able to grow my business.\u0026quot;\u003cbr /\u003e\u003cbr /\u003e\u003ca href\u003d\"http://hugomelo.com/minimalist-marketing/\" class\u003d\"ot-anchor\"\u003ehttp://hugomelo.com/minimalist-marketing/\u003c/a\u003e",1332446837623,"https://web.archive.org/web/20120322202814/http://www.google.com/favicon.ico",[]
,"z12gs10zrzuey3nzt04chb24yurjeftxxqw0k","","s:updates:esshare",[[,,,"How To Market a Minimalist Business",,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,"This week I got to sit down and interview Everett Bogue, a writer and entrepreneur that I really respect, who\u0026#39;s recently rewritten his book Minimalist Business.",,,[,"https://web.archive.org/web/20120322202814/http://hugomelo.com/minimalist-marketing/",,"text/html","document"]
,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,[[,"//web.archive.org/web/20120322202814/https://s2.googleusercontent.com/s2/favicons?domain\u003dhugomelo.com"]
,[,"//web.archive.org/web/20120322202814/https://s2.googleusercontent.com/s2/favicons?domain\u003dhugomelo.com"]
]
