,"//web.archive.org/web/20120322202814/https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-DTGZ0HgahRo/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAB48/rnwhNOjnFmE/photo.jpg",,"I was interviewed by +Hugo Melo about Minimalist Business marketing.\n\nExcerpt from interview: \"The Internet is a vast place. There’s a potential to reach anyone in the world. However, I only want to hear about a product or service if it’s going to benefit me. This is true for everyone. Packaging information is not enough, it needs to be information which benefits other people.\n\nThe only option is to experiment with what we’re putting out into the world. If what I create today doesn’t land, I get an opportunity to try again tomorrow.\n\nThe goal of a Minimalist Business is flexibility. It’s about keeping overhead low so the business can change with a world in flux. It’s by growing, challenging, evolving myself that I’m able to grow my business.\"\n\nhttp://hugomelo.com/minimalist-marketing/","116298207273891385223/posts/ikf6whMZrE4",0,0.0,"./116298207273891385223",[]
,,,"",0,1332446837623661,1,1,,0,1,"0",0,1332446837623,,,0,,,,0,,,,[]
,,,0,0,0,,0,,,,,0,,5,,,[[1,"https://web.archive.org/web/20120322202814/http://hugomelo.com/minimalist-marketing/","//web.archive.org/web/20120322202814/https://s2.googleusercontent.com/s2/favicons?domain\u003dhugomelo.com","How To Market a Minimalist Business","hugomelo.com",,[["https://web.archive.org/web/20120322202814/http://hugomelo.com/minimalist-marketing/","image/jpeg","//web.archive.org/web/20120322202814/https://images1-focus-opensocial.googleusercontent.com/gadgets/proxy?url\u003dhttp://hugomelo.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/03/minimalistbusinessipad-300x3001.jpg\u0026container\u003dfocus\u0026gadget\u003da\u0026rewriteMime\u003dimage/*\u0026refresh\u003d31536000\u0026resize_h\u003d120\u0026no_expand\u003d1",,,,,,"https://web.archive.org/web/20120322202814/http://hugomelo.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/03/minimalistbusinessipad-300x3001.jpg",,,,,,"images",0]
]
,"This week I got to sit down and interview Everett Bogue, a writer and entrepreneur that I really respect, who\u0026#39;s recently rewritten his book Minimalist Business."]
